{
  "texts": [
    "The dataset exhibits several characteristics that makes it particularly suitable for demonstrating our methodology:",
    "Left-Censoring Issues: Approximately 50% of observations fall below the detection limit, creating substantial censoring that must be appropriately handled to avoid biased parameter estimates and predictions.",
    "Importantly, the censored observations show no apparent spatial clustering pattern.",
    "Computational Scale: With n = 136 observations and p = 7 predictors, this dataset represents a moderately-sized spatial problem.",
    "While this scale remains computationally feasible, implementing a full Bayesian inference with latent spatial fields would be prohibitively expensive due to the extensive MCMC sampling required."
  ]
}